          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":15,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"days\":[{\"day_of_week\":0,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest day. Let your body absorb the week ahead. Sleep, hydrate, and enjoy the downtime — recovery is part of training.\"},{\"day_of_week\":1,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run, 20–25 min at 7:00–8:00 /km. This is your aerobic foundation day. Keep it conversational — you should be able to speak in full sentences throughout.\"},{\"day_of_week\":2,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day. Three days of running per week means the days in between matter just as much. Let your muscles repair and adapt.\"},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest or light walking if you feel like moving. No pressure to do anything structured today.\"},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run, 20–25 min at 7:00–8:00 /km. Same effort as Monday — relaxed, steady, and well within your comfort zone. Notice how your body feels compared to earlier in the week.\"},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day before your long run. A short walk is fine, but save your legs for Saturday.\"},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"Long run, 30–35 min at 7:30–8:00 /km. This is the cornerstone of your week. Go slower than you think you need to — the goal is time on feet, not pace. Walk breaks are completely fine and encouraged if needed.\"}],\"week_summary\":\"Welcome to Week 1, Sarah! This first week is all about establishing your rhythm and building the aerobic base that everything else will grow from. At 15 km total, we're matching your current weekly volume — no jump in load, just structure. Three runs, all at easy effort, all within your 45-minute cap. The most important thing this week is finishing each run feeling like you could have done a little more. That feeling is exactly where we want you. What's your sense of how these three days fit into your week?\"}"
        }
      ]
